http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Fishers-go-on-stir-seeking-rehabilitation/article14009990.ece

Fishworkers, including women staged a protest in front of the Secretariat here on Tuesday, demanding rehabilitation of 116 families who were displaced from Valiathura following strong coastal erosion.The protestors tied themselves with fishing nets to register their protest. Father Melkon inaugurated the protest. CPI(M) leader M. Vijayakumar and leaders of the Kerala Swathantra Matsya Thozhilali Federation T. Peter, Anto Elias, Mable Nasyans, Maglene Peter, and James Fernandez spoke. The agitation was called off after Health Minister V.S. Sivakumar promised to issue title deeds to the affected families and implement a housing scheme.